HEADWORD: Phainopepla
<hw>Pha*i`no*pep"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>faeino`s</grk> shining + <grk>pe`plos</grk> robe.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small crested passerine bird
(<spn>Pha⟦ium⟧nopepla nitens</spn>), native of Mexico and the Southern
United States. The adult male is of a uniform glossy blue-black; the
female is brownish. Called also <altname>black
flycatcher</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

